  "doc_id": "40229",
  "text": "A positive HBcAb test is compatible with several scenarios, depending on other markers: acute infection, recovery, chronic infection, false positive. The presence of HBcAb, even without considering the presence of other markers, is considered a valid indicator of prior HBV infection, in epidemiological studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . We decided to study a group of DUs born in Northern Italy, an area with high coverage of HBV universal vaccination. The aims of our study were the following:",
